Development Gap:
    Income Gap:
    - Measured in GDP per capita
    - Use Purchasing Power Parity (PPP) to convert currencies. Exchange rates are based on only tradable goods whereas PPP are based on all goods.
    - Non-tradable goods are cheaper in poorer countries so exchange rates give $1 more value then PPP for poorer countries
    Health Gap:
    - Life expectancy measure
    - Infant morality rate measure (number of deaths before age 1 per 1000 births)
